# Network Layer

## NetworkEnvironment

Environments are defined in `core-network/ktor/NetworkEnvironment.kt`:

```kotlin
enum class NetworkEnvironment(
    val apiHost: String,
) {
    Dev(apiHost = "dev-back-template.com"),
    Prod(apiHost = "prod-back-template.com"),
}
```

Rules:
- `NetworkEnvironment` is the **single** source of API hosts
- Registered in Koin as `factory` via platform module (`expect/actual`)
- Android: resolved from `BuildConfig.FLAVOR` via `AppEnvironmentQualifiers.FLAVOR`
- iOS: injected via `EnvironmentDi.insertKoin(environment)`

## DI Registration

### Common

```kotlin
// core-network/di/CoreNetworkModule.kt
internal expect val platformCoreNetworkModule: Module

val coreNetworkModule = module {
    includes(platformCoreNetworkModule)
}
```

### Android

```kotlin
// core-network/di/CoreNetworkModule.android.kt
internal actual val platformCoreNetworkModule = module {
    factory<NetworkEnvironment> {
        val flavor: String = get(named(AppEnvironmentQualifiers.FLAVOR))
        when (flavor.lowercase()) {
            "prod" -> NetworkEnvironment.Prod
            else -> NetworkEnvironment.Dev
        }
    }
}
```

`AppEnvironmentQualifiers.FLAVOR` is provided by `appModule` in `android/app` from `BuildConfig.FLAVOR`.

### iOS

```kotlin
// core-network/di/EnvironmentDi.kt
class EnvironmentDi : KoinComponent {
    fun insertKoin(environment: NetworkEnvironment) {
        getKoin().declare<NetworkEnvironment>(environment)
    }
}
```

## Ktor HttpClient

Configured in `core-network/ktor/di/CoreNetworkKtorModule.kt`:

```kotlin
val coreNetworkKtorModule = module {
    single<HttpClient> {
        HttpClient {
            // base config: Logging, ContentNegotiation/JSON, HttpResponseValidator
            defaultRequest { setApiHost(environment = get()) }
        }
    }
    factory<KtorClient> { new(::KtorClientImpl) }
}
```

Rules:
- `HttpClient` — `single` (one instance per app)
- `defaultRequest` sets `url.host` and `url.protocol` from `NetworkEnvironment.apiHost`
- SSL certificates configured via `configureCertificates()` for `Dev` environment

## KtorClient

`KtorClient` (from `core-network`) is the typed wrapper over raw `HttpClient`:

```kotlin
interface KtorClient {
    suspend fun <R, D> executeQuery(
        query: suspend () -> HttpResponse,
        deserializer: DeserializationStrategy<D>? = null,
        success: (D) -> Result<R>,
        loggingErrorMessage: String,
    ): Result<R>

    suspend fun get(urlString: String, block: HttpRequestBuilder.() -> Unit = {}): HttpResponse
    suspend fun post(urlString: String, block: HttpRequestBuilder.() -> Unit = {}): HttpResponse
    suspend fun submitForm(urlString: String, formParameters: Parameters, block: HttpRequestBuilder.() -> Unit = {}): HttpResponse
}
```

## ApiClient (feature module)

Each feature creates its own `ApiClient` in `impl/data/network/`:

```kotlin
internal interface {Feature}ApiClient {
    suspend fun getItems(): Result<List<RemoteItem>>
}

internal class {Feature}ApiClientImpl(
    private val ktorClient: KtorClient,
) : {Feature}ApiClient {

    override suspend fun getItems(): Result<List<RemoteItem>> =
        ktorClient.executeQuery(
            query = { ktorClient.get(urlString = "/api/v1/items") },
            deserializer = ListSerializer(RemoteItem.serializer()),
            success = { items -> items.wrapResultSuccess() },
            loggingErrorMessage = "getItems failed",
        )
}
```

Rules:
- `ApiClient` — `internal interface` + `internal class` in `impl` module
- Injects `KtorClient` (not raw `HttpClient`)
- Deserialization via `DeserializationStrategy` (not inline reified)
